## Summary
Add DAG unit executor (`run_dag_units.py`) that reads a JSON manifest and generates AgilePlus-conformant spec.md and work-package files, enabling automated pipeline execution for the epic_F compute/infra epic.

## Context
The DAG foundation epic (epic_F) needs a script that can consume a structured DAG manifest and produce the full set of specification and work-package artifacts following AgilePlus conventions. This PR delivers unit F2 — the executor that wires the DAG processing pipeline into the agileplus workspace.

## Changes
- **`scripts/run_dag_units.py`** — new Python script that:
  - Reads a DAG manifest JSON with `epic`, `title`, `units` (unit_id, title, type, description, dependencies, subtasks)
  - Validates the manifest: no duplicate unit_ids, all required fields present
  - Generates `specs/<epic>/spec.md` — epic-level specification with unit table
  - Generates `specs/<epic>/tasks.md` — aggregated work-package index
  - Generates `specs/<epic>/tasks/WP<unit_id>.md` — individual WP files with AgilePlus YAML frontmatter (work_package_id, lane, dependencies, subtasks, history)
  - Generates `specs/<epic>/meta.json` — metadata file
- **`scripts/test-manifest-epic_F.json`** — test manifest with F1 and F2 units
- **`specs/epic_F/`** — generated output for the test manifest

### Key Implementation Details
- Follows AgilePlus WP00-style work-package format exactly (YAML frontmatter with `work_package_id`, `lane`, `dependencies`, `subtasks`, `phase`, `history`)
- Duplicate unit_id detection runs before any file writes, preventing partial output
- All files are UTF-8 encoded per AgilePlus CLAUDE.md policy
- Output respects the `specs/<epic>/tasks/` directory structure used by existing AgilePlus specs

## Use Cases
- Automate work-package creation from DAG execution plans
- Ensure consistent spec/WP format across all epic_F units
- Validate unit manifest integrity before pipeline execution
- Enable CI/CD to consume the generated spec artifacts

## Testing
```bash
# Run against the test manifest (validates output generation)
python scripts/run_dag_units.py scripts/test-manifest-epic_F.json --output-dir .

# Test duplicate detection
python scripts/run_dag_units.py <manifest-with-duplicates> --output-dir .
# Expected: exits with code 1 and error message identifying the duplicate
```

